Package cp213

Class DoubleQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • cp213.DoubleQueue
  • public class DoubleQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    A queue structure of Movie objects. Only the Movie values contained in the queue are visible through the standard queue methods. The Movie values are stored in a DoubleLink object provided in class as attribute.
    Version:
    2019-10-08
    Author:

    • Method Detail

      • combine

        public void combine​(DoubleQueue source1,
                    DoubleQueue source2)
        Combines the contents of the left and right Queues into the current Queue. Moves nodes only - does not move value or call the high-level methods insert or remove. left and right Queues are empty when done. Nodes are moved alternately from left and right to this Queue.
        Parameters:
        source1 - The front Queue to extract nodes from.
        source2 - The second Queue to extract nodes from.

      • insert

        public void insert​(Movie value)
        Adds value to the rear of the queue.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to added to the rear of the queue.

      • remove

        public Movie remove()
        Returns the front value of the queue and removes that value from the queue. The next node in the queue becomes the new front node.
        Returns:
        The value at the front of the queue.

      • peekFront

        public Movie peekFront()
        Returns the value at the front. Must be copy safe
        Returns:
        the value at the front.

      • peekRear

        public Movie peekRear()
        Returns the value at the rear. Must be copy safe.
        Returns:
        the value at the rear.

      • toArray

        public final Movie[] toArray()
        Returns all the data in the queue in the form of an array.
        Returns:
        The array of Movie elements. Must be copy safe
